Class LogProperty.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter

java.lang.Object
io.jstach.rainbowgum.LogProperty.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter
All Implemented Interfaces:
LogProperty.PropertyGetter<String>
Enclosing interface:
LogProperty.PropertyGetter<T>
public static sealed class LogProperty.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter extends Object implements LogProperty.PropertyGetter<String>
A property getter and builder that has no conversion but may prefix the key and search recursively up the key path.

While you can map the string properties with LogProperty.PropertyGetter.map(PropertyFunction) it is preferred to use the of methods on this class for basic types especially for list or map types as the implementation will call the implementation specific in LogProperties. An example is ofMap() which will call the LogProperties implementation of LogProperties.mapOrNull(String).
